export const Questions = [
  {
    prompt: "Inside which HTML element do we put the JavaScript?",
    optionA: "<javascript>",
    optionB: "<scripting>",
    optionC: "<script>",
    optionD: "<js>",
    answer: "<script>",
  },
  {
    prompt: "How do you create a function in JavaScript?",
    optionA: "function = myFunction()",
    optionB: "function myFunction()",
    optionC: "function:myFunction()",
    answer: "function myFunction()",
  },
  {
    prompt: "How to write an IF statement in JavaScript?",
    optionA: "if i = 5 then",
    optionB: "if i == 5 then",
    optionC: "if i = 5",
    optionD: "if (i == 5)",
    answer: "if (i == 5)",
  },
  {
    prompt: "How does a WHILE loop start?",
    optionA: "while i = 1 to 10",
    optionB: "while (i <= 10)",
    optionC: "while (i <= 10; i++)",
    answer: "while (i <= 10)",
  },
  {
    prompt: "How does a FOR loop start?",
    optionA: "for i = 1 to 5",
    optionB: "for (i = 0; i <= 5)",
    optionC: "for (i <= 5; i++)",
    optionD: "for (i = 0; i <= 5; i++)",
    answer: "for (i = 0; i <= 5; i++)",
  },
  {
    prompt: "How do you round the number 7.25, to the nearest integer?",
    optionA: "rnd(7.25)",
    optionB: "Math.round(7.25)",
    optionC: "round(7.25)",
    optionD: "Math.rnd(7.25)",
    answer: "Math.round(7.25)",
  },
  {
    prompt: "what's her least favorite drink?",
    optionA: "red wine",
    optionB: "white wine",
    optionC: "beer",
    optionD: "rose",
    answer: "red wine",
  },
  {
    prompt: "What's her zodiac sign?",
    optionA: "Taurus",
    optionB: "Gemini",
    optionC: "Aries",
    optionD: "Cancer",
    answer: "Gemini",
  },
  {
    prompt: "What blood type she has?",
    optionA: "A",
    optionB: "B",
    optionC: "O",
    optionD: "AB",
    answer: "A",
  },
  {
    prompt: "What do you want to say to her?",
    optionA: "i love you",
    optionB: "i miss you",
    optionC: "you are my favorite person",
    optionD: "all the above",
    answer: "all the above",
  },
];
